label is retired.

== Generator — parameterized self-domain fix ==

Format is the corpus's only parameterized self-domain (Format[T], domainAspect.typeName =
itself). Two coupled gaps, latent since 96d39ac: isDomain compared domainAspect.typeName by
full TypeName equality (which includes type parameters the self-reference omits), so Format
fell through to the leaf path; and domainGlobal emitted the container as the bare object name
(Domain[Format], which would not compile). Fix: isDomain compares name + package only;
domainGlobal emits the container through wildcardTypeName (Domain[Format[_]]). Both are no-ops
for every non-parameterized domain.

== Slice B — World transformation service ==

The chapter-46 semantic core (Position -> Observable -> Location, meaning preserved) is wired
into a running Pekko actor graph: Aerial.Input (decode loose PositionReport Json -> typed
Position) -> World.Consumer (the transform interior; geodesy concentrated here) -> World.Provider
(routing) -> Terrestrial.Output (encode typed Location -> loose LocationReport Json) ->
Terrestrial.Consumer -> sink. WorldTransformServiceTest runs a PositionReport(51.5, -0.12,
35000 ft) through the whole graph and recovers the world point (lat/lon < 1e-6, 35000 ft ->
10668 m). All four actors are definition-backed (their own JSON); only the irreducible
Pekko/Evrete/geodesy bodies stay hand-written, awaiting the JSON-rules (#2) and Generator
actor-emission fold (#3) precursors to TransformBuilder.

== Test-output logging migration ==

Bulky println floods the IntelliJ sbt console and overwrites the start of a full run. New
draco.PersistentTestLog (mix-in) exposes `log` (SLF4J test.output, routed by a SiftingAppender
on a per-suite MDC key to target/test-output/<suite>.log, truncated each run, never on the
console) and `console` (a clean one-line headline). ScalaTest's per-test PASS/FAIL still shows
(via sbt's logger, not stdout), plus one pointer per suite. All println-heavy suites migrated
(println -> log.info); YAMLRoundTripTest keeps only its one-line summary on the console.
Shipped/test-support actors (NaturalActor, EgoActor) use a class logger at debug. CLI/tools/demos
keep println, since their stdout is the product (CLI, GeneratorCLI, scripts/*, RETEExample).

